  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed rear dormer, by reason of its height, bulk, location and design, would be overly dominant on the rear roofslope to the detriment of the character and appearance of the host building and the Victoria Park Conservation Area. As such the proposal is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design led&amp;nbsp; approach), D4 (Delivering good design) and HC1 (Heritage Conservation and Growth) of the London Plan 2021, policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) of the Hackney Local Plan 2020 and the recommendations of the Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Extensions and Alterations 2009.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "The proposed ground floor extension by reason of height and depth would represent an unneighbourly development which would result in an overbearing impact and loss of light and outlook for neighbouring residents contrary to policy LP2 (Development and Amenity) of LP33 (2020) and policy D6 (Housing quality and standards) of the London Plan 2021"
  ],
